.--'--'-.    It is about the /etc/passwd file.

 
The /etc/passwd file in Linux is a system file that stores user account 
information, such as username, user ID, group ID, user info, home directory 
location and default shell.

The fifth field is the so called 'gecos' field, that holds user info, such
as full name, phone number or job title.

Now go ahead... What is the phone number of user 'john' on the system?  

